<div id='communityQuestionsWithAnswers'>
<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1024162-i-m-confused-on-the-reading-order-for-this">I&#39;m confused on the reading order for this series - I&#39;m hearing a lot about Thieves World and characters form this book appearing there. Can someone recommend the best reading order for these books? Is it best to go chronologically or start with Sacred Band and then go to Thieves World? Thanks!</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1024162'><a id="like_count_community_question_1024162" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/1024162?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">4 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F8617107-the-sacred-band">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/1024162-i-m-confused-on-the-reading-order-for-this">4 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/1024162-i-m-confused-on-the-reading-order-for-this">Add your answer</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/8847159-janet-e"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_100x100-6433b08cbe793211f55e184d39e84c4d.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/8847159-janet-e">Janet E.</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Happy to help. You can read the Sacred Band of Stepsons books several ways. You can start with The Sacred Band, and then read The Fish the Fighters an<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Happy to help. You can read the Sacred Band of Stepsons books several ways. You can start with The Sacred Band, and then read The Fish the Fighters and the Song-girl. OR you can go in what we consider chronological order: 1st, Beyond Sanctuary; 2nd, Beyond the Veil; 3rd Beyond Wizardwall; 4th Tempus; 5th The Sacred Band; 6th, The Fish the Fighters and the Song-girl. If you chose the first order suggested above, you'll read the newest stories first (that's what I would do), and then return to the beginning with Beyond Sanctuary and read: 1st Beyond Sanctuary; 2nd, Beyond the Veil; 3rd Beyond Wizardwall; 4th, Tempus; 5th The Sacred Band, and 6th, The Fish the Fighters and the Song-girl. Now, there are also three volumes of the series that haven't been released yet in e-book or trade paper, and they were written to work as an elliptical loop and come back to the main chronology after the book Tempus and before the book The Sacred Band. Those three (as yet available only as old mmpbs) are, in order, City at the Edge of Time; Tempus Unbound; and Storm Seed. When the last three are revised and updated, we will renumber the entire series. We're doing the Author's Cut revisions on those three now, and I suggest you wait for their republication, which covers the time that the Stepsons were disbanded, and their subsequent reformation. - jem<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

