              <span id="reviewTextContainer898566949" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9699011832775705105">Took a bit to get into it, what with all the action and the many names and characters, who have many names. But after about 30 pages in, I finally was able to start comprehending this incredible &apos;Band&apos;. The writing is rather stilted, making you pay close attention, feels like it&apos;s being translated from an ancient tome to modern English, which added to the appeal for me. Lines like &quot;Some daylight remained, even if the light had that pearly quality of supernal tantrums abating.&quot; Graphic, violent y</span>
  <span id="freeText9699011832775705105" style="display:none">Took a bit to get into it, what with all the action and the many names and characters, who have many names. But after about 30 pages in, I finally was able to start comprehending this incredible 'Band'. The writing is rather stilted, making you pay close attention, feels like it's being translated from an ancient tome to modern English, which added to the appeal for me. Lines like "Some daylight remained, even if the light had that pearly quality of supernal tantrums abating." Graphic, violent yet almost poetic, this is a series I'm going to enjoy indeed.<br /><br />Special thanks to Walter Rhein and Sarah Hulcy for introducing me to this series. Many thanks actually!</span>
